  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Automatic parameter configuration in an I5.0 contextAs mentioned, I5.0 integrates most technological concepts from its predecessor, I4.0, while prioritizing human wellbeing and ecosystem preservation.",
    "In one of our previous works, we presented how, thanks to I4.0 concepts, a factory developed an auto-parameter configuration scheme for its production.",
    "The system allowed the factory to closely track its production, regulate parameters required to meet daily targets, and engage in overtime production runs when to reach the target.",
    "In the I4.0 context, the essential condition to meet to initiate the automatic parameter configuration and to run overtime was to compare the final actual production count and the daily target through the overtime percentage set by the factory [53].",
    "In an I5.0 environment, we include two additional factors in the production process: the factory pollution rate and the maximum overtime working hours for employees."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
